  "texts": [
    "Notably, within the exercise groups, significant differences were observed only in the indicators of physical functioning and general health in patients undergoing the HIIT protocol compared to MICT.",
    "These improvements persisted through the 6-and 12-month follow-up assessments in both exercise groups.",
    "In contrast, the group that did not undergo any exercise intervention did not experience significant improvements in QoL.",
    "These results show that community-based exercise CR programs, even at moderate intensity, can play an important role in improving QoL.",
    "This is especially significant given the influence of CAD on an individual's QoL, often associated with increased functional dependence (Cuerda et al. 2012)."
  ],
